1:
I will give thanks to Yahweh with my whole heart;
\q I will tell about all your marvelous deeds.
\q

5:
You rebuked the nations;
\q you have destroyed the wicked;
\q you have blotted out their name forever and ever.
\q

7:
But Yahweh remains forever;
\q he has established his throne for justice.
\q

11:
Sing praises to Yahweh, who rules in Zion;
\q tell the nations what he has done.
\q

15:
The nations have sunk down into the pit that they made;
\q their feet are caught in the net that they hid.
\q

16:
Yahweh has made himself known; he has executed judgment;
\q the wicked is ensnared by his own actions.
\qs Selah\qs*

19:
Arise, Yahweh; do not let man win against you;
\q may the nations be judged in your sight.
\q

20:
Terrify them, Yahweh;
\q may the nations know that they are mere men.
\qs Selah\qs*
